The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, April 30, 2007

 Roads to avoid

 All major thoroughfares between 11 am and noon. Trinamul Congress will organise roadblocks to protest the Nandigram killings.

 All major roads in between Deshapriya Park and Bijon Setu, 3 pm. Ananda Marga Pracaraka Samgha will organise a procession.

 School

 Calcutta International Schools new campus at Anandapur, off Ruby General Hospital, will be inaugurated, 5.30 pm. Followed by an art auction.

 Book 

 Bengal Divided: The Unmaking of a Nation (1905-1971) by Nitish Sengupta will be released at Raj Bhavan, 4 pm. 

 Music

 Concert featuring Regis Gizava and David Miranando, at Princeton Club, 7.30 pm.

 Sarod recital by Ranajit Sengupta at Calcutta School of Music, 7 pm.

 Sports

 Inter-club sports carnival, in association with The Telegraph, at Saturday Club, 4 pm.

 Art show

 Works of Somnath Hore, at Galerie 88, 3 pm.




